-- BayernLB’s Hungarian MKB Unit Names Simak to Replace CEO Erdei
-- B y   A n d r a s   G e r g e l y
-- 2012-02-15T14:52:44Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-15/bayernlb-s-hungarian-mkb-unit-names-simak-to-replace-ceo-erdei.html
 Pal Simak, deputy chief executive
officer of  Bayerische Landesbank (BLGZ) ’s MKB Bank Zrt. unit in
 Hungary , will replace Tamas Erdei, who quit as CEO, the bank
said in an e-mailed statement today.  Erdei, who has worked at MKB since 1983 and has led the
bank since 1994, served as president of Hungary’s Bank
Association for almost 15 years, MKB said. Simak worked as a
financial consultant at McKinsey & Company before joining MKB.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andras Gergely in Budapest at 
 agergely@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
